==English==
====Etymology====
*[[cinder]] + [[Ella]]

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Cinderella'''

# The main [[character]] in the [[fairy tale]] of the same name, a [[mistreat]]ed and [[impoverished]] girl. At a [[royal]] [[ball]] she meets a handsome [[prince]] who later identifies her with a dropped article, most commonly a [[slipper]], and removes her from her poverty.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{cattag|by analogy}} A mistreated and impoverished girl.
# ''(Attributive):'' rising unexpectedly from obscurity to success, as a '''Cinderella team'''.
# (''Philately''): A [[stamp]] or stamp-like [[label]] issued for purposes other than [[postal]] administration, not issued by a central government, or not listed in most general catalogues.
#:'''Usage note:''' Not all authorities are uniform in what they consider to be Cinderellas.

